      <div class="msgContentFrame">This topic just so happen to come up in a few conversations the past few weeks. All of them concerned 3 women (all U.S. Army Captains) who have separate bank accounts from their husbands. Their reasoning was that they make more money than them. One even has a pre-nup. <br /> <br />I always thought that was something &quot;taboo&quot; in non-celebrity lives. I understand having separate accounts AND a joint account, but these women JUST have completely separate accounts.Is this old fashioned thinking or is this another double standard from society? Is it more acceptable for a woman to initiate that rather than a man, especially when the partner has significantly less amount of money?  <br /><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>Bardalicious agrees with Almalieque {12 July 2010} <br />&quot;You just spewed geek gibberish at me.&quot; -Barking Turtle</div></div>
