      <div class="msgContentFrame">My husband and I have &quot;our own&quot; bank accounts, but we are both signers on those accounts. I pretty much manage our money and I make sure he's got enough in his account for whatever he needs. The bills get paid out of my account, for the most part.  <br /> <br />I don't believe in keeping your finances a secret from your partner, personally. I'm not sure if you were implying that the women you spoke to were trying to do that or not. When I was a kid, my mom used to take me to the store, and when we'd go to pay, she'd pull out a credit card and look at me and say, &quot;Don't tell your step-dad about this card.&quot; Then, sure enough, come the end of the month she'd give me a check to deposit in my account and ask me to write a check to pay for the bill. It made me wary, and I never wanted to be like that.  <br /> <br />ETA: So there's no confusion, when I say &quot;keeping your finances a secret form your partner,&quot; I only mean once you're married.  <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Nov 21st 2010  9:33pm by Belkira </span></i><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><span class="sm"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Kurt Vonnegut (1922-2007) wrote:</div><div class="orig"> I am eternally grateful.. for my knack of finding in great books, some of them very funny books, reason enough to feel honored to be alive, no matter what else might be going on. </div></div></span></div></div>
