      <div class="msgContentFrame">As far as I'm concerned a joint bank account is asking for trouble, unless you are both disciplined spenders.  In a couple, I don't think that you should be keeping large monetary secrets from each other.  But I think each person being responsible for their half of the finances is the way to go.  If one person is on significantly less money than the other, then as a couple it wouldn't be harmonious to keep the money unequal.   The days when all the money belonged to the man are a hang over from when his wife was his possession also.  There was a long trailing hangover where women weren't seen as intelligent and responsible enough to handle important finances.  These days men and women get equal educations, so how a couple wants to handle finances should come down to an equal partnership, however arranged to suit the couple. <br /> <br />My ideal is for each person to give the other half their income after tax is taken out.  Then both people have exactly the same amount to manage.  Each person should pay half the bills on time, and finance half the large property/items owned in common.  Apart from that, each person is responsible for saving some in the way they are most comfortable with.  Each person spends the rest of their own half on necessities and pleasures.  If the couple ever splits, they've already owned and managed the money and goods half-half.  Each person would walk with the savings and items that they accumulated during the partnership (and the original things they owned before the partnership).  If they frittered away their half of their money entirely on ephemerals, then too bad.  <div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><a href="HTTP://robotmonster.bandcamp.com/track/the-space-between-the-stars" rel="external nofollow" title="robotmonster.bandcamp.com/track/the-space-between-the-stars">Profits on this chillout-single help pay my book and gaming addictions!</a> <br /> <br /><a href="HTTP://robotmonster.bandcamp.com/album/alien-communication" rel="external nofollow" title="robotmonster.bandcamp.com/album/alien-communication">And I think this one is a work of genius.  Of course, I'm biased</a></div></div>
