      <div class="msgContentFrame">Having separate accounts is a smart move. A third &quot;Joint Account&quot; might be ok to cover things like house payments and bills. Separate can save you or your other half the grief of dealing with a large loss of money when things go bad in a relationship. Imagine having your check go to a joint account and then finding it empty plus the possibility of it even being changed to their name. Poof! You just lost everything! Also, Never, never, let your new significant other talk you into having your checks to into &quot;Mother's&quot; bank account! My Idiot sister did that and she lost everything and two more paychecks from the Army when things went bad.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><a href="http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v619/ImGatomon/Request.jpg" title="http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v619/ImGatomon/Request.jpg" rel="external nofollow">http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v619/ImGatomon/Request.jpg</a> <br />Iamadam the Shady wrote: <br />The karma system is working as intended. <br /> <br /><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">PaladinStargazer wrote:</div><div class="orig"> <br />For someone that claims to not care about karma you sure bring it up a lot. I honestly couldn't give a sh*t about my karma. It's colors, that's it.</div></div></div></div>
