      <div class="msgContentFrame">Though I'm not technically married yet, the gf and I do live together and use a joint account for our joint expenses. This has worked well so far, allowing us to use it for groceries, rent, utilities, and the occasional night out. We still keep separate accounts for personal purchases and for the majority of eating out. I guess the most important thing is communication. I pay all the bills, but I make sure she knows when I do it. Sometimes I'll think we should use the joint account to pay for a night out (tickets to a play for example), but I make sure she's ok with it first. We also both check our account balances fairly regularly so as to not have any surprises.  <br /> <br />It may work better for us since we make almost the same amount anyway, though, and both agree to how much we are both putting in to the account each month. Not that we particularly care about it being even, but I think it helps keep resentment or bad feelings from brooding. <div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>Links to other Alla forums you may not know about! <br /><a href="/forum.html?forum=5" rel="external nofollow" title="wow.allakhazam.com/forum.html?forum=5">The Anime/Manga (and other things) Discussion forum!</a> <br /><a href="/forum.html?forum=22" rel="external" title="wow.allakhazam.com/forum.html?forum=22">The Gaming Forum</a></div></div>
