      <div class="msgContentFrame">When I got married the first time, we had a joint account and no other. Looking back (and forward), I would not do that again. It makes perfect sense to me for each spouse to have their own account into which their pay is deposited. Then, by mutual agreement, a percentage of that pay should be deposited into a shared account for bills, groceries, etc... <br /> <br />Of course, this arrangement only works when both spouses do. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Nov 22nd 2010 10:34am by BrownDuck </span></i><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><span class="sm">R.I.P. Jessica M. 5/3/2010</span> <br /></div></div>
