      <div class="msgContentFrame">I agree with what the majority has said. I think each person should have their own separate accounts, but at the same time share an account for smaller things. <br /> <br />Now, the question is do you differentiate having separate accounts while having mutual access to both and just one account? <br /> <br />For me, while they may be similar, I have no problem with the former but wouldn't want to do the latter just for money managing reasons. Right now, I actually have a bank that's designated for all local bills and I think that's the way to go. I just don't think it's safe to be the sole person able to access the primary account. As I'm not married, I have my mom on my account just in case. I've actually had to use her a couple times, so I definitely think that was a smart move. So, I would think the same would apply for a couple as well.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>Bardalicious agrees with Almalieque {12 July 2010} <br />&quot;You just spewed geek gibberish at me.&quot; -Barking Turtle</div></div>
