      <div class="msgContentFrame">Joint, always. <br /> <br />It's family money.  We discuss our budget and what's left for spending, I manage the money so I show her where it's going and what's left over then I'll typically ask if there's anything extra she needs so I can make sure I don't spend that money and I'll tell her what I'm spending (&quot;have to pay for my game this week hon&quot;) and what's left is joint spending money (whoever needs something outside of what was planned, say lunch money, spends it) and we both keep an eye on the account both knowing what needs to be in there at any given time. <br /> <br />I don't know how people do it otherwise.</div>
